suggestions.value:
Intro:
it seemed so sincere, like it was true love
like, do you understand, or is it all above

Verse 1:
nights like this, i can't take no more,
you wanna leave, but i'm begging you to stay some more.
they see us comin', they got that hump like a camel
but we ain't fazed, we keep it real, never trampled
and when we roll through, we say 'dei', that's our sign
ain't nobody gonna stop us, our stars align.
the brothers are coming, they're bringing the heat,
vasoconstrictors losing their grip, time we all meet.

Pre-Chorus 1:
we're up all night, no time to rest,
but we'll make it look easy, we'll ace the test.

Chorus 1:
shining like that, yeah we're blinding the scene
my mercedes ride by em, all this dough, green.
party all night, let the good times roll,
never let it stop, lost in the vibes, on a roll.

Verse 2:
we gonna party on right through the night,
ain't nothin' gonna stop us, we stayin' hype,
the more he talked to me, i couldn't keep it on mute,
you want a lifeline? you gotta find your own truth.
she was so scared, yeah she started to panic,
if jesus walked by, she'd be hypnotic.
we posted on that block, let our names be known,
for the haters that try, we won't die alone,

Pre-Chorus 2:
she was on the floor, moving to the beat,
dogg pound bumpin', got her feeling real heat,

Chorus 2:
no place like home, where the love and comfort reside,
so good to be home again, no more running and hiding.
i turn my swag on, gotta show off my style,
they all with it, can't be put on trial,

Chorus 3:
make it happen, do it like that, we the elite,
this beat a fine tune, making them move to the beat.
let's get high, this is our mission,
in this prohibition, we're on a new edition.

Bridge:
my crew gets whatever they want, they got the power,
living it up in la, can't erase you from my mind, like a never- ending shower.
sometimes she plays hard to get, but i know it's all a game
she can't hide her laughter, i know she wants the same

Outro:
baby, why you gotta put me in a situation,
got me feelin' like i'm drowning, no salvation,

Instrumental:
straight outta oakland, green day represent,
through all these crazy days, no regrets, that's evident.

Verse 1:
got my barbie and ken, we playin' house,
they always follow my lead, no doubt.
all my homies are invited, so let's go,
if you believe, we can take this show.
they try to tell us how to live, by the book that they think they read,
but we ain't followin' their rules, we got our own lead,
john sinclair, yeah we'll keep smokin', livin' how we please,
we don't care what they sayin', we'll do it with ease.

Pre-Chorus 1:
maybe we let go, time to break free,
they wanted heaven from me but i couldn't guarantee.

Chorus 1:
listen to the children, screaming in the street,
gotta let me run, to see who came undone, feeling the heat.
got them vibes down in la,
come on, girl, let's get that good sookie,

Verse 2:
and alright, i'm in the war room, feeling lost and low,
need to ask cupid, where did all my love go?
got a maid who does all the chores, so i don't have to lift a finger,
we ain't gonna stop living, just to appease the haters and linger.
in the party we da la, sippin' hennessy,
your eyes all lazy, but you make me feel good mentally.
and we walk a few miles, just to be where she is,
do you wanna take it there, show me that you're mine and hers?

Pre-Chorus 2:
on this windy road, twistin' and turnin', we don't know where we're gonna end
but we don't care, we just let it go, trustin' the journey we send

Chorus 2:
i'm tired of this power shit, it's overrated,
now i'm ready to rise again, leave my past faded.
riding by the water, feeling so fly,
like i'm parachuting on the ultimate high.

Chorus 3:
my boys always get whatever they need,
can't erase you from my thoughts, you're stuck in my mind like a weed.
niggas on me, ridin' round your side of town,
they thinkin' they can bring me down, but i won't drown.

Bridge:
my arms are reaching out for you,
'cause that's the physical, you're my desire.
they can't handle the real, just let it go and be free,
they keep watchin', but they don't gotta see,

Outro:
she taught me how to pimp my game up,
showed me the way, six hunnid, what's up?

Instrumental:
why you acting so distant, can't you see?
all these niggas 'bout to fall flat, that's where they'll be.

Verse 1:
you know the truths, they can't be denied,
and when you've wandered in, you'll see it with your own eyes,
we're just having a ball, livin' life to the fullest,
not lettin' anyone hold back our gorgeousness.
turn off the lights, put your hands in the air,
with these island girls, oh what a feeling, we don't have a care.
i curl into a ball, just gotta breathe,
keep it peaceful, let your essence seethe.

Pre-Chorus 1:
lemme show you who's the real villain,
these chains 'round my neck got me feeling like i'm imprisoned.

Chorus 1:
we stand tall, never gonna fall,
live it up, that's just how we ball.
toys are fun, but can you be real for once?
i ain't got time for games, just wanna feel your touch.

Verse 2:
if i stay, i'll feel the touch of fallen tears,
but when it's all said and done, i'll conquer my fears.
just put the shoe on, let's go for a ride,
and the more we talk, you know i can't hide,
you know you make my world light up,
i can't help but smile, i can't stifle my love.
justin timberlake on the mic,
you think i'm just kidding, yo, you don't understand.

Pre-Chorus 2:
strictly for the caddy lovers,
you know i do it like you thought i would,

Chorus 2:
now i got millions on mills, but they can't buy me peace,
the devil's here to fool ya, don't fall for his deceit.
she got me ridin' on her bone,
head wandered in, got me thinking 'bout taking her home,

Chorus 3:
they help me escape, forget all the pain,
in their arms, my troubles go down the drain,
now we riding high, ain't nothing gonna bring us down.
we always bouncing that shit, make the beats clap,

Bridge:
what can i say to him, to make him see,
this is where everyone's at, place to be.
this weight on my back, i gotta lift it all
i'm chasing my dreams, giving it my all.( 205 being a reference to weightlifting competitions where athletes lift weights with numbers as titles)

Outro:
no matter what y'all do, you can't bring me down,
my girl got me feelin' amazing, like a queen with her crown.

Instrumental:
love is a mystery, it's like a stranger,
but true romance, it's forever, it never falters or wavers.

Intro:
taking the keys to that caddy, gonna hit the road
but before i go, gotta say, i love y'all, you're my bros.

Verse 1:
you walked out, left me just your shoes,
but from this vantage point, we see the madness, no excuse.
she got that body just right,
ain't no need for all that glittering light,
'cause she shines on her own,
so let's make this night our own.
you're my smokey's man, always rolling us up,
if i had one wish, it'd be to hear your songs forever without a let up.

Pre-Chorus 1:
can you forgive me now you won, or are you still mad?
are we gonna start again, try to make things right and not so sad?

Intro:
got these niggas on me, can't shake 'em off,
and all that you say is getting tossed and lost.

Verse 1:
on top of the game, got my crown shining bright,
all the bitches wanna be in my sight.
can they handle the truth, will they ever see,
the way she moves, sweetly moaning, driving me crazy.
reminisce and i yearn, take me back oh into the days,
nostalgic feeling as i ride these musical waves.
she's so perfect, ain't no denying
but what goes on underneath, it's terrifying

Pre-Chorus 1:
got so much money, but it don't mean a thing
without you, my heart just can't sing.

Chorus 1:
now you old, and i'm still young and wild,
gunshots ranged out like a bell, while we chase the piles.
boy, you got a rep, but watch me break it,
i'll lose myself, ain't no one gonna take it.

Verse 2:
they wanted you to fall, they wanted you to break,
something so childish, oh how long will it take,
she acting savage, never showing no remorse.
it caught me by surprise, didn't see it comin' at all
but now we're livin' it up, havin' a ball, standing tall
just goes to show, life's full of surprises
gotta make the most out of every single day, no compromises.
love can consume and turn you sour,

Pre-Chorus 2:
we out here makin' chess moves, like we don't care,
they say we could live forever, no despair.

Chorus 2:
twistin' paper planes, watch it glide,
dirty money all up in my hands, gotta let it ride,
it could be love or it could be lust, i don't really care, just let me bust.
we don't need no fake friends around us,

Chorus 3:
take me back, oh, to the good old days,
he told me he had no answer, just a daze,
now is all we get, let's make it count,
gotta live in the moment, can't let it amount.

Bridge:
at the end of the night, i'm still standing
yall niggas be knowin', my bars are outstanding
stay true to myself, never compromising.
tell him he can't compete with what i got,

Outro:
and i'm black, that's a fact,
got me feeling things, your body right on track.

Instrumental:
nights like this, i'm feeling so fly,
oh yeah, you just gotta ask why.

Intro:
heeey, baby girl, i love the way you move
you got no mechanic, you're a natural groove.

Verse 1:
oh lord, bet you've seen it all,
ten million views and then some more.
we flew up so high, no one could reach us,
you lookin' like the way you did before, love, no need for fuss.
i know for sure, i can't go on without you,
these nights like this, all i do is dream of you.
can you imagine how it feels to be so real,
you gotta be special to know how this all feels.

Pre-Chorus 1:
i'm living it up, no time for doubt,
i'll keep pushing, let me ride it out.

Chorus 1:
got my spirulina, gonna stay healthy and clean,
she can play my guitar, make the strings sing.
you so fit, my oh my
lord, i bet you have me hypnotized

Verse 2:
gunshots ranged out like a bell on my block,
but you make me feel so good, like taking shots from a glock.
this year's been wild, 2020, it's true,
but when you tell me you want me, oh what a feeling, i know i want you too.
all i want is someone to fall in love with me,
cause sometimes, this life can be so lonely,
but it ain't about to stop me, from chasing my dreams,
even if they call it something so childish, so extreme.

Pre-Chorus 2:
sara's coming back and my heart starts to race,
in 2020 things got wild, had to go crazy,

Chorus 2:
life gets chaotic, like runnin' through traffic,
be a careful creature, avoid the damage.
took the mic out my basement, know you heard me
now i'm spittin' fire, setting the world on fire, you'll see.

Chorus 3:
and she perfect, don't you see?
take some time off, follow my lead, be carefree.
lost in the city, so sometimes i feel alone,

Bridge:
gotta stay true to myself, no matter what they say,
even when they confrontin' me, diggin' at the truth that's underneath.
you can't deny our crew's the best in town,
we hold it down, that's why we wear the crown.

Outro:
so move like vampires, let's dance the night away,
what is your name, can i be your prey?

Instrumental:
rap game, what we talkin' 'bout? money and fame, it seems,
but them lacs don't define us, we'll drink up all your potion, chase our dreams.
